        "timestamp": "2019-01-28 15:17:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Thanks!\n > - I'll be happy to see if failing tests will fail the verification\n > - Will Sonar report the coverage?\n > - Not sure, but isn't Gulp bit old?\n\n- I made some changes to show that build fails when tests are incorrect. \n- Unfortunatelly haven't time to investigate how to pass coverage results to sonar but we can add jest-sonar-reporter plugin which should be able generate correct report for sonar as well.\n- I am not an js expert, but talked with few guys from out JS projects and they suggested to use gulp (btw I considered only grunt which is quite old tool and gulp). And at first sight it is really easily configurable, so I liked it ;)",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
