        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-28 15:55:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\n> > Thanks!\n > > - I'll be happy to see if failing tests will fail the\n > verification\n > > - Will Sonar report the coverage?\n > > - Not sure, but isn't Gulp bit old?\n > \n > - I made some changes to show that build fails when tests are\n > incorrect.\n > - Unfortunatelly haven't time to investigate how to pass coverage\n > results to sonar but we can add jest-sonar-reporter plugin which\n > should be able generate correct report for sonar as well.\n > - I am not an js expert, but talked with few guys from out JS\n > projects and they suggested to use gulp (btw I considered only\n > grunt which is quite old tool and gulp). And at first sight it is\n > really easily configurable, so I liked it ;)\n\nOk, failed test looks nice! :)\n\n```\n17:18:10 [ERROR] FAIL src/main/webapp/app/vid/scripts/controller/aaiSubscriberController.test.js\n17:18:10 [ERROR]   TreeCtrl testing\n17:18:10 [ERROR]     ✓ adds 1 + 2 to equal 3 (29ms)\n17:18:10 [ERROR]     ✕ adds 1 + 2 to equal 4 (12ms)\n```\n\nAdditionally, Gulp seems good for what we need here, so great.\n(I think webpack is more common todays, but we only need a tasker, not a packaging system.)\n\nBTW, while building I see \"gulp.run() has been deprecated. Use task dependencies or gulp.watch task triggering instead\".\n\nBottom line, I think this small demo is very nice.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
